# The attempt to insert the remaining iron ore into the furnace failed because I no longer have any iron ore in my inventory. 
# This indicates that the iron ore was not properly transferred from my inventory to the furnace after the initial smelting process.

# Step 9: Resolve the issue
#
# I need to gather more iron ore to continue smelting and crafting iron plates. 
# Let's move to the nearest iron ore resource again and collect more.

move_to(nearest(Resource.IronOre))  # Move to the nearest iron ore resource
harvest_resource(nearest(Resource.IronOre), quantity=10)  # Gather more iron ore
print(f"Updated inventory after iron ore collection: {inspect_inventory()}")  # Check inventory again

# Now that I have iron ore, I can insert it into the furnace for further smelting.
insert_item(Prototype.IronOre, furnace, quantity=5)  # Insert 5 units of iron ore into the furnace
print(f"Final furnace state after inserting more ore: {inspect_inventory(furnace)}")  # Check the furnace inventory again
print(f"Final inventory: {inspect_inventory()}")  # Check my own inventory again
